IRS990.ActivityOrMissionDesc: NYSTEC IS A NOT-FOR-PROFIT TECHNOLOGY CONSULTING COMPANY, ADVISING ORGANIZATIONS, AGENCIES, INSTITUTIONS, AND BUSINESSES. NYSTEC'S MISSION IS TO PROVIDE SUPERIOR CONSULTING SERVICES TO ASSIST STATE AND GOVERNMENT CLIENTS IN SUCCESSFULLY IDENTIFYING, DEFINING, ACQUIRING AND IMPLEMENTING TECHNOLOGY NEEDS. WE PROVIDE SERVICES THAT LEVERAGE THE TECHNOLOGY BASE IN NEW YORK STATE TO DEFINE, DEVELOP AND ENHANCE HIGH-TECH INNOVATION, KNOWLEDGE, AND CAPABILITIES THROUGHOUT GOVERNMENT AND INDUSTRY.

SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE CORPORATION FILES FORM 990 ANNUALLY WITH THE INTERNAL REVENUE SERVICE. WHEN ANNUAL RETURNS ARE FILED, SOME TAX POSITIONS TAKEN ARE HIGHLY CERTAIN TO BE SUSTAINED UPON EXAMINATION BY THE TAXING AUTHORITIES, WHILE OTHER TAX POSITIONS ARE SUBJECT TO UNCERTAINTY ABOUT THE TECHNICAL MERITS OF THE POSITION OR AMOUNT OF THE POSITION'S TAX BENEFIT THAT WOULD ULTIMATELY BE SUSTAINED. MANAGEMENT EVALUATED THE CORPORATION'S TAX POSITIONS, INCLUDING INTEREST AND PENALTIES ATTRIBUTABLE THERETO, AND CONCLUDED THAT THE CORPORATION HAD TAKEN NO TAX POSITION THAT REQUIRED ADJUSTMENTS IN ITS FINANCIAL STATEMENTS AS OF SEPTEMBER 30, 2023 AND 2022.

SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: NYSTEC HIRES AN HR CONSULTING COMPANY TO PREPARE A COMPENSATION STUDY FOR THE CEO, OFFICERS AND DIRECTORS, AND ALL OTHER EMPLOYEES. THE CONSULTING COMPANY WORKS FROM A SET OF ASSUMPTIONS (REVENUE SIZE, NUMBER OF EMPLOYEES, LOCATION, NOT-FOR-PROFIT STATUS, SERVICE AREA) TO DEVELOP A RELEVANT PEER GROUP IN ORDER TO COMPARE BASE COMPENSATION, INCENTIVES AND RETIREMENT CONTRIBUTIONS TO MARKET AVERAGE. RECOMMENDATIONS ARE MADE AS A RESULT OF THIS PROCESS, AND ADJUSTMENTS ARE DISCUSSED AND IMPLEMENTED. THE BOARD OF DIRECTORS APPROVES THE CEO SALARIES.
